  "texts": [
    "To depict the process of engagement with our customized LLM, we employ a UML activity diagram, which outlines the workflow for interaction between the software engineers and the LLM (Fig. 1).",
    "Software Requirements DocumentsWithout a foundation of high-quality requirements as input, even the most performant LLM can be rendered useless.",
    "Instead of typing a few informal itemized requirements to an LLM, we require the software development team to upload to the LLM structured requirements in the format of project glossary (Google Docs), vision and scope (Google Docs), and use cases (Google Docs).• Project Glossary: This document contains definitions of all key terms used within the project, ensuring clarity and consistency across all project communications and artifacts.• Vision and Scope: This outlines the overall objectives, the scope of the project, and the roles of different stakeholders, providing a comprehensive overview of the project's goals and expected outcomes.",
    "Software Engineer Tailored GPT Upload requirements Object-Oriented Design Project Glossary Vision and Scope Use Cases Requirement Summary </> Test Cases </> Code Analyze the requirements Request to derive functional requirements Derive the functional requirements Functional Requirements Request to generate design Generate OO Design Request to generate test cases and code Generate test cases and codeFig. 1.",
    "A human software engineer's interaction with the tailored GPT model.• Use Cases: This document includes detailed descriptions of each use case, illustrating specific functionality that the software is expected to perform."
  ]
}